The '''ratchet-tailed treepie''' ('''''Temnurus temnurus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the crow and jay family [[Corvidae]]. The species is also known as the '''notch-tailed treepie'''. It is [[monotypic]] within the genus '''''Temnurus'''''.<ref name="HBW604">{{cite encyclopedia  | last = dos Anjos| first = Luiz  | editor-last = del Hoyo  | editor-first = Josep  | editor2-last = Elliott  | editor2-first =Andrew  | editor3-last = Christie  | editor3-first =David  | title = Family Corvidae (Crows)  | encyclopedia = [[Handbook of the Birds of the World]]  | volume = 9. Bush-shrikes to Old World Sparrows | publisher = Lynx Editions  | location = Barcelona  | year = 2007}}</ref>

The species has a [[disjunct distribution]] in Southeast Asia and China. One population is found in southern Thailand, another in southern Vietnam, another in central and northern Vietnam and Laos, and the last in [[Hainan]] in China. Its natural [[habitat]] is [[tropical]] moist broadleaf evergreen lowland [[forest]]s, and secondary forest and scrubland.<ref name="HBW604"/>

